20are%20on%20track%20to%20lose%20an%20average%20of%2011.9%20years%20of%20life%20expectancy%20compared%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation's%20(WHO)%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20by%20India's%20own%20national%20standards%2C%20the%20residents%20stand%20to%20lose%208.5%20years%20of%20life%20expectancy%20if%20current%20pollution%20levels%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%2C%20the%20capital%20and%20most%20populous%20city%20of%20India%2C%20also%20holds%20the%20dubious%20distinction%20of%20being%20the%20most%20polluted%20city%20globally%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20report%20also%20said%20if%20India%20were%20to%20meet%20its%20national%20PM2.5%20standards%2C%20life%20expectancy%20for%20Delhi's%20residents%20could%20increase%20by%208.5%20years%20and%20if%20it%20met%20the%20WHO%20standards%2C%20nearly%2012%20years%20could%20be%20added%20to%20the%20life%20expectancy%20of%20Delhi's%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM2.5%2C%20a%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20that%20can%20penetrate%20deep%20into%20the%20respiratory%20system%20and%20trigger%20respiratory%20problems%2C%20is%20a%20significant%20health%20risk%20and%20a%20major%20contributing%20factor%20to%20pollution%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20underscores%20that%20the%20annual%20PM2.5%20standard%20in%20India%20is%20set%20at%2040%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre%2C%20yet%20more%20than%2040%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20population%20is%20exposed%20to%20air%20that%20exceeds%20this%20limit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20in%20Delhi%20on%20Wednesday%20settled%20at%2034%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20which%20is%20normal%20for%20this%20time%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20weather%20department%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20(IMD)%2C%20the%20humidity%20level%20stood%20at%2085%20per%20cent%20at%205%3A30%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Met%20department%20has%20issued%20a%20%26quot%3Byellow%2